 for my testing needs. I need to ensure there’s a public top-level class, and it's essential to have a one-to-one mapping for my file names. I’m wondering if I should name the test file DefaultAllocationManagerOptionTest.java. Should I remove any placeholders I have in there? I could use a bash command to remove unnecessary files and don’t forget to update my build.gradle accordingly!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_fEASkU8XNWsaPZnxiFhPqrHW|fc_0d822cf5ea0740010169f7062c420881969f4c444efcb4d89b", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.arrow/arrow-memory-core/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_apache_arrow/arrow_memory_core/DefaultAllocationManagerOptionTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_apache_arrow.arrow_memory_core;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport org.apache.arrow.memory.DefaultAllocationManagerOption;\nimport org.apache.arrow.memory.RootAllocator;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class DefaultAllocationManagerOptionTest {\n    @Test\n    void rootAllocatorUsesConfiguredNettyAllocationManager() {\n        String previousAllocationManagerType = System.getProperty(\n                DefaultAllocationManagerOption.ALLOCATION_MANAGER_TYPE_PROPERTY_NAME);\n        System.setProperty(DefaultAllocationManagerOption.ALLOCATION_MANAGER_TYPE_PROPERTY_NAME, \"Netty\");\n        try (RootAllocator allocator = new RootAllocator(1024)) {\n            assertThat(allocator.getLimit()).isEqualTo(1024);\n            assertThat(allocator.getAllocatedMemory()).isZero();\n        } finally {\n            restoreAllocationManagerType(previousAllocationManagerType);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void restoreAllocationManagerType(String previousAllocationManagerType) {\n        if (previousAllocationManagerType == null) {\n            System.clearProperty(DefaultAllocationManagerOption.ALLOCATION_MANAGER_TYPE_PROPERTY_NAME);\n        } else {\n            System.setProperty(\n                    DefaultAllocationManagerOption.ALLOCATION_MANAGER_TYPE_PROPERTY_NAME,\n                    previousAllocationManagerType);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 753, "output": 954, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27307, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777796641395, "responseId": "resp_0d822cf5ea0740010169f70621d6a8819692d932bd4dac2c5b"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_fEASkU8XNWsaPZnxiFhPqrHW|fc_0d822cf5ea0740010169f7062c420881969f4c444efcb4d89b", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1598 bytes to tests/src/org.apache.arrow/arrow-memory-core/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_apache_arrow/arrow_memory_core/DefaultAllocationManagerOptionTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777796653595}]}
